Lagos – Super Eagles and Leicester striker, Kelechi Iheanacho has been described as a “beast in the air” by teammate, goalkeeper Kasper Schmeichel. The Nigerian capped his man of the match performance with his first Premier league goal for Leicester on Saturday in the 4-1 defeat of West Brom. And he has continued to receive plaudits since Saturday with his teammate Schmeichel describing him as a beast. He was singled out for praises even from his coaches and team mates and was voted man of the match despite that he spent less than 30 minutes in the match, scoring one of the goals and assisting another. Taking to his twitter handle, Kasper Schmeichel, praised Iheanacho and called him the beast of the air after his powerfully nodded ball beat the West Brom goalkeeper for The Foxes’ third goal. “Happy for my man @67Kelechi for his performance and great goal. You’re a beast in the air   Great result today for us.” Meanwhile, national team mate, Wilfred Ndidid, had earlier celebrated Iheanacho, saying that he was happy with the former Manchester City star. He wrote in his twitter handle thus. “Back to winning ways and congrats to my guy on his goal and assist @67Kelechi Thanks to the fans for their great support.” 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE.  100% Natural Solution To Premature Ejaculation, Weak Erection, Watery Sperm, Other Sexual Dysfunctions And Last More Than 30 Minutes During Sex.